esp32-brother-ptouch
Copyright 2026 Jack Hosemans

This product includes software developed with reference to:

- treideme/brother_pt (https://github.com/treideme/brother_pt), Apache-2.0.
  Used as the hardware-verified reference implementation of the Brother
  raster protocol; this component's command streams are validated byte-exact
  against it (see host/gen_oracle.py).

- packbits 0.6 by Mikhail Korobov (https://github.com/kmike/packbits), MIT.
  ptouch_packbits_encode() in src/ptouch_raster.c is a C port of that
  package's encoder state machine (including its run-boundary quirks), so
  generated raster streams match the brother_pt reference byte-for-byte.

Protocol facts are from the Brother "Raster Command Reference"
(PT-E550W / P750W / P710BT).
